analysis: The documents all pertain to the establishment of wildlife refuges and breeding grounds, primarily for migratory birds, in various states across the US. They delineate specific areas of land and water to be reserved for the Department of Agriculture or the Department of Interior for conservation purposes. Many of the documents include legal descriptions of the land being set aside, and prohibitions against hunting, trapping, or disturbing wildlife within the designated areas. Some documents also address existing rights and uses of the land, such as those related to water projects or prior agreements.
title: Migratory Bird and Wildlife Refuges
